<p>Goal is a textbox for the Date, glyphicon button to start datepicker that accepts existing text, Jan 1, 2015 or March 3, 2015 or 3/3/15 or 3/3/2015 convert any to one format, 01/01/2015.</p>  <p>Seems simple but the button appears to have the effect of 'registering' the textbox as a datepicker, where am I going wrong?  Datepicker does not show a close or clear button, it will not disappear when clicked. In the View,</p>  <pre><code>      &lt;div class="form-group"&gt;             @Html.LabelFor(model =&gt; model.Astr, new { @class = "control-label col-md-3" })             &lt;div class="col-md-9"&gt;                 @Html.EditorFor(model =&gt; model.Astr, new { @class = "CreatedOn" })                 @Html.ValidationMessageFor(model =&gt; model.Astr)              &lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;         &lt;label class="input-group-btn" id="ddd" onclick="setCalendar()"&gt;             &lt;span class="btn btn-default"&gt;                 &lt;span class="glyphicon glyphicon-calendar"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;             &lt;/span&gt;         &lt;/label&gt; </code></pre>  <p>This matches the asp/mvc model thats already working;  The script has bootstrap datepicker (datetimepicker did not work)        </p>  <pre><code>&lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;     function setCalendar()     {         alert("///");         $('#Astr').datepicker("show",{             format: "MM d, yyyy",             clearBtn: true,             autoclose: true         }).on('changeDate', function (e) {             $(this).datepicker('hide')          });      } &lt;/script&gt;                    &lt;script type="text/javascript"&gt;                 $(function () {                     $('#Astr').on('click', function (e) {                         alert("clicked");                         var st = $('#Astr').val();   // document.getElementsByName('Astr').value;//(text.target).text(); alert(text);                         var dt = new Date(st);                         var day = dt.getDate();                         // alert(day);                         var year = dt.getFullYear();                          var mi = dt.getMonth() + 1;                         var mytxt = mi + '/' + day + '/' + year;                         //st.value = mytxt;                         $('#Astr').val(mytxt);                     }); </code></pre>